.env
__pycache__/
*.pyc
venv/
.DS_Store
# NOTE: market_snapshot.json is intentionally NOT ignored — market_data.yml
# commits it (git add market_snapshot.json) as the cloud routine's data source.
# NOTE: fills.json is intentionally NOT ignored either — STEP 4 of the routine
# writes it as the durable broker-fill accumulator and `git add`s it. If it were
# ignored, the authoritative record of which orders the broker ACCEPTED would
# never reach the remote, so a crash after STEP 4 could not be reconciled from
# fills.json (only by re-querying get_equity_orders). Keep it tracked.
performance_report.json
# NOTE: the forecast ledger — forecasts.jsonl, forecasts_scored.jsonl,
# agent_scorecards.json — is intentionally TRACKED (not ignored). It is the
# measurement harness's append-only evidence clock and MUST accumulate across runs.
# It was previously ignored, so the routine's `git add` was a silent no-op and every
# cloud run's forecasts were lost (the feed froze at 2026-06-18). The routine now
# commits these files (ROUTINE_DAILY_CYCLE.md STEP 5) — same lesson as fills.json.
# NOTE: factor_history.jsonl is likewise intentionally TRACKED — the full-universe
# point-in-time factor time series appended by fetch_snapshot.py and committed by
# market_data.yml (GH Actions is the only plane that scores the whole universe
# daily). It is the substrate for factor-persistence / IC; do NOT ignore it.
# Analysis / recovery artifacts — regenerated from logs on demand.
deliberation_stats.json
reconciliation_report.json
# A12 reproducibility manifest + exported prompts (regenerated each run from
# analysis.py constants) and B16 append-only health history.
reproducibility.json
prompts/
health_history.jsonl
# FMP/SEC provider cache — populated in CI via actions/cache. Transient locally
# (SEC EDGAR blocks residential IPs; use workflow_dispatch full_refresh=true to seed).
provider_cache.json
# Resumable universe-fetch cursor (universe.next_batch). Transient operational
# state — persisted across GH Actions runs via actions/cache, not committed.
fetch_progress.json
# NOTE: data_quality_report.json + data_quality_history.jsonl are intentionally
# TRACKED (§15.2) — the report is the cloud routine's + heartbeat's data-quality
# gate input, and the history .jsonl is the time series the weekly digest trends.
# market_data.yml commits both; do NOT ignore them (same lesson as factor_history).
# heartbeat_report.json is transient — written only inside the heartbeat.yml run
# for its github-script step to read; never committed.
heartbeat_report.json
# NOTE: research_dossier.json + events.jsonl are intentionally TRACKED (Phase 4,
# §12) — the dossier is the ONLY artifact the Wednesday cloud agents read (built by
# build_dossier.py, committed by market_data.yml); events.jsonl is the append-only
# event time series the dossier synthesizes from. Do NOT ignore them.

# Paper drafts and reviewer notes — pre-publication, not part of the codebase.
PAPER_DRAFT.md
PAPER_ARXIV.md
PAPER_C.md
PAPER_C.tex
*.tex
RESEARCH_THESIS.md
REVIEWER_FEEDBACK_BACKLOG.md
REVIEWER_FEEDBACK_PLAN.md
eval/

# NOTE: the routine's data + audit files (portfolio_snapshot.json, trades.csv,
# transactions.json, decision_journal.json, agent_log.json, system_health.json,
# mcp_portfolio.json, mcp_market_data.json, pending_decisions.json,
# fundamentals_cache.json, portfolio_peak.json) are intentionally TRACKED. The
# cloud routine commits them via explicit `git add`, and publish.yml triggers on
# a portfolio_snapshot.json push. Do NOT gitignore them — an ignored file makes
# the routine's `git add` a silent no-op (stages nothing), breaking the daily
# commit/claim/publish path. Portfolio data for the $500 demo account is public
# by design; the sensitive values (account number, API keys, routine IDs, MCP
# connector UUID) are redacted in code/docs instead.
